      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOUNDING CHIEF (8) drawn the outside box and could get a clear run. Was below best last time when 6th and beaten 6 lengths at The Meadows (30.62). Goes very well at course and distance boasting four wins. Worth another chance. ATHENS AURA (7) turned spotting a big start finishing fourth (26.15) last time in a Grade 5 at Shepparton. Form at the trip sound including five wins. Bold showing expected. REMI JOY (3) led throughout when winning two back then got further back last time but came home hard into third and beaten 4 lengths at Geelong (26.29). Has won two of five starts from this draw. Can measure up. RANGER'S GIRL (2) is right in the mix.",
